<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="124" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Chen" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Chen" box="[653,1000,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minipenis">
<emphasis box="[653,804,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">D. minipenis</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Chen
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuoh" authorityName="Kuoh" box="[1071,1286,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piceatus">
<emphasis box="[1071,1206,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">D. piceatus</emphasis>
Kuoh
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from them by its aedeagus in ventral aspect with a shorter spinous basal process, and paired long basal processes dorsally sinuate in lateral aspect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="124" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Etymology.</emphasis>
New species name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName box="[915,1067,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multidentatus">
<emphasis box="[915,1067,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">multidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the many toothlike aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
